reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for HPZ230
reviews.reviewText: Got a used HPZ230 for cheap and used the guts for a rackmount server. I needed to upgrade the 400Watt Power supply to a 800Watt to handle all 24 disks. This cable solved that propriority issue perfectly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I saw bad reviews for other adapters designed to connect a standard ATX power supply to an HP workstation motherboard, so I was concerned this adapter might also be problematic. However, this one was highly recommended and I can confirm it works perfectly for my use! My old workstation works great with a new power supply.Edit: This is a positive edit! After months of use the system with this adapter is still working perfectly and reliably. I can definitely recommend this for anyone needing to adapt a standard ATX power supply to the proprietary HP connector.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The only one that works for me
reviews.reviewText: I was a building a budget server with used parts. I needed a power adapter for HP Z420 motherboard to work with standard ATX power supply. I tried a few adapters and this is the only one working for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2021
reviews.reviewText: I am fond of building mining rigs with old workstation components. I usually go with Lenovo motherboards because they are quirk-free. But occasionally I go with Dell. Unfortunately, you need adapters for their non-standard configurations. This is a high quality adapter that I felt comfortable putting in a budget gaming build that would max out the power handling capabilities of the motherboard. The wires seem like they are a gauge larger than what is strictly necessary and fit and finish of the connectors are very good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Used to Install New Power Supply for HP Z220
reviews.reviewText: Used for new after-market 650 watt power supply installed on a HP Z220 i5 without any problems. Needed for gaming GPU that required 8 pin power connector.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked flawlessly with Corsair RM750
reviews.reviewText: I was very worried that I might fry something using an adapter and power supply that wasn't officially supported for my machine, but I ended up having no issues at all. If you need an adapter to use an ATX power supply in an HP Z210 CMT, this is one that I can recommend.
